  "title": "Grand Canyon Star Party 2026, June 6 -13 - Grand Canyon National Park (U.S. National Park Service)",
  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_828672\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_5987700_828672\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481828\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_5987700_481828\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Grand Canyon Star Party 2026, June 6 - 13</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6803528\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt=\"The white Milky Way over a red lit parking lot with people and telescopes.\" src=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/Still-6.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title=\"The center of the Milky Way galaxy glides over a red lit parking lot filled with people and telescopes. Grand Canyon Star Party is held every year in June.\"/>\n<figcaption>Grand Canyon National Park is one of the best places in the world to enjoy pristine night skies. </figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6157005\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6157005\">\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7584095\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7584095\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<p>Not able to attend Grand Canyon Star Party? No worries! We offer astronomy programs year-round! Check out our <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/upcoming-night-sky-events.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=7556730,upcoming-night-sky-events.htm,11006|\">Upcoming Night Sky Events page</a>.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6389231\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6389231\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2><strong>Things to Know about the 2026 Star Party</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Attend this free, open to the general public, event. The <a href=\"https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/fees.htm\" id=\"https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/fees.htm|\">park entrance fee</a>, is good on both South and North rims for 7 days. No additional tickets or sign-up is required.</li>\n<li>\n<p>The event begins at sunset, although the best viewing is after 9 pm and many telescopes come down after 11 pm; however, on nights with clear, calm skies, some astronomers continue sharing their telescopes into the night.</p>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/camping.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=2638417,camping.htm,11006|\">Campground</a> or <a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/lodging.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=1878476,lodging.htm,11006|\">lodging</a> reservations are recommended. </li>\n<li>Dress warmly. Temperatures drop quickly after sunset—even during summer months.</li>\n<li>View an assortment of planets, double stars, star clusters, nebulae and distant galaxies by night, and perhaps the Sun or Venus by day.</li>\n<li>Skies will be starry and dark until the moon rises the first night. It rises progressively later throughout the week of the Star Party.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Bring a Red Flashlight</strong></h3>\n<p>Make your way safely: use a red flashlight; white flashlights and cell phone lights are discouraged on the telescope lot. Make a red flashlight by:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Covering any flashlight with red cellophane; a limited supply of cellophane and rubber bands are available prior to the evening presentations at the Grand Canyon Visitor Center.</li>\n<li>Painting the flashlight lens with red nail polish or a red magic marker.</li>\n<li>For more on why red flashlights are helpful, and how the human eye works after dark,  <a href=\"/articles/dark-adaptation-of-the-human-eye-and-the-value-of-red-flashlights.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6389262,dark-adaptation-of-the-human-eye-and-the-value-of-red-flashlights.htm,30335|\">click here.</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6309730\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6309730\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-right\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/IMG_0534e.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"a starry night. a family is gathered around a large telescope as an astronomer is talking. Everyone is bathed in red light.\" src=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/IMG_0534e.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"Grand Canyon Star Party - South Rim\"/>\n</picture>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h2><strong>South Rim Star Party 2026</strong></h2>\n<p>Events include nightly evening programs from special guest speakers at 8:00 pm outdoors, in the plaza in front of the Visitor Center. The speakers and program topics are listed below, To get a good seat arrive early —seating is limited. Bring a folding chair, or cushions to sit on. <br/>\n<br/>\nThe evening programs are followed by telescope viewing in the large lot behind the Visitor Center. Follow the red rope lights to the telescope lot.<br/>\n<br/>\nPark rangers offer constellation tours at 9:00, 9:30, and 10:00 pm. The evening program, constellation tours, and at least one telescope are wheelchair accessible.<br/>\n<br/>\nPlan on driving your vehicle and parking in Visitor Center lots 1 through 4, since the last Village (Blue) Route shuttle is at 9:30 pm. Lot 4 provides the nearest accessible parking. <br/>\n<br/>\nThe South Rim Star Party is sponsored by the Tucson Amateur Astronomy Association.<br/>\n<br/>\nAmateur astronomers from across the country volunteer their expertise and offer free nightly astronomy programs and telescope viewing during this special annual event.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5987708\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5987708\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2><strong>Star Party Evening Programs (South Rim)</strong></h2>\n<p>Presentations take place outdoors in the plaza in front of the Visitor Center. Presentations start at 8 pm. (Limited-capacity seating - so bring a folding chair or cushions to sit on.)</p>\n<h2>Saturday, June 6</h2>\n<h4><strong>What's Up in the Night Sky?</strong></h4>\nLearn about all the amazing phenomena one can see with the naked eye and through telescopes in an International Dark Sky Park!<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>David Eicher - Former Editor in Chief, Astronomy Magazine</strong>\n<h2>Sunday, June 7</h2>\n<h4><strong>Protecting The Night</strong></h4>\nDiscover the ways Northern Arizona is leading the way in protecting some of the best night skies on planet Earth.<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Dr. Danielle Adams - Flagstaff Dark Skies Coalition</strong>\n<h2>Monday, June 8</h2>\n<h4>Tour of the Universe: You are Here</h4>\nTake a tour from planet Earth to the outer edges of the Universe in this dar out talk!<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Dean Regas - Author, host of Looking Up podcast</strong>\n<h2>Tuesday, June 9</h2>\n<h4><strong>Star Dance</strong></h4>\nExperience traditional dances from the Zuni Pueblo, including the Star Dance!<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Cellicion Zuni Dancers</strong>\n<h2>Wednesday, June 10</h2>\n<h4><strong>Hopi Cosmos</strong></h4>\nLearn about the Hopi cosmos through the lens of award-winning Hopi art.<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Gerald Dawavendewa - Hopi artist</strong>\n<h2>Thursday, June 11</h2>\n<h4><strong>Astronomy Talk</strong></h4>\nTBD<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Dr. Logan Pearce, Astronomer, University of Michigan</strong>\n<h2>Friday, June 12</h2>\n<h4><strong>Astronomy Talk</strong></h4>\nTBD<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Laura-May Abron, Griffith Observatory</strong>\n<h2>Saturday, June 13</h2>\n<h4><strong>Paiute Astronomy</strong></h4>\nLearn about the intricate and beautiful astronomy of the Southern Paiute peoples.<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Autumn Gillard - Paiute astronomer, Paiute Indian Tribe of Utah</strong><br/>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6157030\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6157030\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h3>Constellation Talks (South Rim)</h3>\n<p><strong>Constellation talks happen every night of the event: 9, 9:30 and 10 pm</strong></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5987706\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5987706\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-right\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/NR-Star-Party.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"Twilight; lluminated by red light, a group of people are looking through telescopes on the veranda of a rustic lodge.\" src=\"/grca/planyourvisit/images/NR-Star-Party.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"NR Star Party\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Telescope viewing on the veranda of Grand Canyon Lodge on the North Rim <p class=\"figcredit\">Photo courtesy of Christian Schroll</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<h2>North Rim Star Party 2026</h2>\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>Due to the Dragon Bravo Fire, there will be no Star Party on the North Rim in 2026.</strong></span><br/>\n<br/>\n<s>Telescopes are set up on the porch of the Grand Canyon Lodge every evening. An astronomy related evening program will be presented at 7:30 pm in the auditorium of Grand Canyon Lodge. Check park bulletin boards for the evening program schedule.<br/>\n<br/>\nConstellation talks are also given throughout the evening.<br/>\n<br/>\nBy day, look for solar telescopes set up at various locations.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe North Rim Star Party is sponsored by the Saguaro Astronomy Club of Phoenix, Arizona.</s></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7529604\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7529604\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Star Party Evening Programs (North Rim)</h2>\n<p><s><strong>North Rim Lodge Auditorium</strong><br/>\nPresentations start at 7:30 pm. (Limited-capacity seating)</s><br/>\n<br/>\n<span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>Due to the Dragon Bravo Fire, there will be no Star Party on the North Rim in 2026.</strong></span></p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6389189\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6389189\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Become a Volunteer in 2026</h2>\n<p>All amateur astronomers interested in sharing the skies with visitors are invited to participate. Whether you can volunteer for a few days or the whole event, you can help to enrich the lives of people from all over the world.<br/>\n<br/>\nFind volunteer opportunities for day and night telescopic outreach, visual and imaging, laser guided constellation tours, demonstration toolkits and auditorium presentations. <strong>Registration as a volunteer is required</strong> and can be done through the following site:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sign up for the <strong>South Rim</strong> Star Party with the <a href=\"https://tucsonastronomy.org/grand-canyon-star-party/\" id=\"https://tucsonastronomy.org/grand-canyon-star-party/|\">Tucson Amateur Astronomy Association.</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5987710\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5987710\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2><strong><font color=\"#556b2f\">Questions?</font></strong> <a href=\"/common/utilities/sendmail/sendemail.cfm?o=5984DFBE8FECA3BD9ABE33A1E904E5AA498B&amp;r=/grca/planyourvisit/grand-canyon-star-party.htm\" id=\"/common/utilities/sendmail/sendemail.cfm?o=5984DFBE8FECA3BD9ABE33A1E904E5AA498B&amp;r=/grca/planyourvisit/grand-canyon-star-party.htm|\">E-mail</a></h2>\n<p><strong>Rader Lane - Dark Skies Program Manager</strong><br/>\nGrand Canyon National Park<br/>\n</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5987711\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5987711\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Future Star Party Dates </h2>\n<p>2026: June 6 - 13<br/>\n2027: May 29 - June 5<br/>\n2028: June 17 - 24<br/>\n2029: June 2 - 9<br/>\n2030: June 22 - 29<br/>\n2031: June 14 -21<br/>\n2032: June 5 -12<br/>\n2033: June 18 - 25<br/>\n2034: June 10 -17<br/>\n2035: June 2 - 9<br/>\n</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6309860\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6309860\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Star Party and Night Sky Videos</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/night-spoken-series.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6103527,night-spoken-series.htm,14075|\">Night Spoken Series</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/virtual-grand-canyon-star-party-2020.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=6801434,virtual-grand-canyon-star-party-2020.htm,11006|\">Video Presentations from Virtual Grand Canyon Star Party 2020</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/virtual-grand-canyon-star-party-2021.htm\" id=\"https://www.nps.gov/grca/planyourvisit/virtual-grand-canyon-star-party-2021.htm|\">Video Presentations from Virtual Grand Canyon Star Party 2021</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9y2yJiSHPqM\" id=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9y2yJiSHPqM|\">North Rim Star Party Video by the Planetary Society</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5987714\"